  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A hemolysis index validation requirement mandates a controlled experiment as the required verification method; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational study drawing on post-market clinical registry data. The narrative throughout this package presents the observational cohort data as functionally equivalent to a controlled bench experiment, citing flow-rate stratification and propensity-score adjustment as surrogates for experimental control. Readers familiar with the registry protocol may not immediately detect that the structured activityType field records 'observational-study' rather than the 'controlled-experiment' mandated by the requirement. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven fall below required levels consistent with MRL 5 gap findings. Decision recorded as Accepted on the basis of the validation narrative without resolving the method mismatch.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
